The per-engine sea-level thrust of the F-1 is 6770 kN (kilonewtons).

This value is explicitly recorded in the SysML v2 model definition of the 'F-1' part:

```sysml
part def 'F-1' :> RocketEngine {
	doc /* A single-chamber liquid-propellant rocket engine, the most powerful ever built, used in the S-IC first stage. */
	attribute thrustSeaLevel :> ISQ::force = 6770 ['kN'];
	attribute :>> thrustVacuum = 7770 ['kN'];
	attribute :>> specificImpulseVacuum = 421 ['s'];
}
```

The attribute `thrustSeaLevel` is the direct declaration of this performance characteristic within the formal model structure.
